iii_difficulty_bermud_song.value:
In order to cheer up the crew, I started singing an old song: {
} “... We are all just prisoners here {
} Of our own device ...” {
} But they became even more scared for some reason.

iii_difficulty_crab_song.value:
I started singing my favorite song: {
}“I am a [starship ^ spaceship] {
} And [I am^my systems are] OK {
} I fly all light night {
} And I fly all light day.”{
} But the captain told me to shut up, and we kept silent the rest of the way.

iii_difficulty_sargas_song.value:
In order to cheer them up, I sung them a song, which I’ve heard when we were in the New Ireland star cluster: {
}“... Now in this bog there was a starship.{
}A rare ship. A rattling ship.{
}Ship in the bog{
}And the bog down in the valley-o...”{
} But they only became enraged.

iv_darklady_1var.value:
– I do! – said the captain. – Your reign brings only harm, and heaps of dust everywhere. You cannot fly from one star to another for all this dust – you cannot even see the space! Humans don’t want to cooperate with other humanoids. You cannot refuel or repair your starship. And you cannot even buy spare parts. The only thing you hear from everywhere is all this “darkness” and “beauty” stuff! Actually, forget spare parts – you can’t even buy food in a grocery store!
– Your accusations are absurd as well as monstrous! You will be [burned to ashes^dismantled down to molecules^turned into molecular dust], and behold [the full power of my anger^my terrible beauty^the darkness that lurks behind all things], not necessarily in that order! – answered the Lady. – But because of your courage, seeing as you weren’t afraid to come here, I’ll give you a tiny chance to survive. Write me a report of things that are happening in the Universe, and make it 50 thousand words – no less! I’ll give you a [day ^ month]. If your accusations prove to hold at least a grain of truth – I’ll spare you, and send you to clean the dust in my palaces. And if they won’t – well, you’ll have only yourself to blame.

{iv_darklady_final}

